---
description: "Writing recipe instructions, three-phase cooking workflow, Already Prepped / Sous Chef / Chef sections, markdown bold italic emphasis, delegation structure for meals"
alwaysApply: false
---
# Recipe Instruction Format

Guidelines for structuring recipe instructions in the three-phase workflow format that matches the household's actual cooking process.

**Context loading:** If not already loaded, read `brainstorming/idea-basis/cooking-identity.md` for the cook's equipment, technique preferences, and delegation style.

**Gold-standard template:** `brainstorming/idea-basis/prototype-week.md` is the canonical reference for instruction structure. Follow its pattern.

<rule>
name: recipe-instruction-format
description: Three-phase instruction structure for meal recipes

philosophy:
  context: "Recipes should reflect the real workflow - what's prepped ahead, what helpers do, and what the primary cook finishes"
  goal: "Clear delegation and timing for efficient weeknight cooking"

instruction_structure:
  phases:
    already_prepped:
      label: "### Already Prepped"
      format: "H3 heading followed by bulleted list"
      purpose: "Sunday prep components used tonight -- what's in the fridge/freezer ready to go"
      examples:
        - "**Green beans** (sesame-dressed bag) in fridge from Sunday."
        - "**Soy eggs** in marinade in fridge from Sunday."
        - "**Ground pork** (mapo portion) in freezer from Sunday."
    
    sous_chef:
      label: "### Sous Chef - Assembly"
      format: "H3 heading followed by paragraph instructions"
      purpose: "Tasks done before chef starts active cooking"
      examples:
        - "Start rice in the rice cooker"
        - "Drop bags in sous vide bath to come to temp"
        - "Prep fresh components (smash cucumbers, shred cabbage)"
        - "Boil noodles, portion pickled items"
      notes:
        - "Label flexes: 'Sous Chef - Assembly', 'Sous Chef - Prep', etc."
        - "Instructions should be clear enough for any family member"
    
    chef_cooking:
      label: "### Chef - Wok Sequence" or "### Chef - Cooking"
      format: "H3 heading followed by paragraph instructions"
      purpose: "Active cooking by primary cook -- wok, cast iron, oven"
      label_flexes:
        - "### Chef - Wok Sequence (for wok nights with multiple dishes)"
        - "### Chef - Cooking (for single-technique nights)"
      notes:
        - "End with a **Table**: line describing the final table layout"
        - "For wok nights, label each dish: **Wok dish 1 -- [name]**, **Wok dish 2 -- [name]**"

formatting_rules:
  already_prepped:
    - "Use bulleted list format"
    - "Start each item with ' - ' (space, dash, space)"
    - "Be specific about storage location and state"
    - "Example: ' - Flat iron steaks have been seasoned and vacuum sealed. Stored in fridge.'"
  
  sous_chef:
    - "Use clear, actionable paragraphs"
    - "Specify temperatures when using sous vide"
    - "Note when Chef will control remotely"
    - "Be explicit about cutting techniques (e.g., 'through the core so wedges hold together')"
    - "Include timing when relevant"
  
  chef_finishing:
    - "Write in active, direct style"
    - "Include sensory cues (golden, crispy, reduced, thickened)"
    - "Describe plating composition"
    - "Note any saucing or garnishing"

recipe_patterns:
  wok_night:
    already_prepped: "Sous vide cai bags in fridge, soy eggs, frozen protein portion"
    sous_chef: "Rice on, warm bags, prep fresh cai (smash cucumbers, portion pickles)"
    chef: "Wok sequence -- 1-3 dishes fired in a row, each into a shared serving dish"
  
  prep_and_heat:
    already_prepped: "Formed patty/meatballs, soup cubes, pickled items"
    sous_chef: "Rice cooker with steam rack for patty, reheat bags, prep fresh items"
    chef: "Gwuntong from cubes, one quick wok dish, assemble table"
  
  chef_dish:
    already_prepped: "Seasoned protein (vacuum sealed), sous vide cai bag"
    sous_chef: "Drop cai bag in bath, make fresh slaw, start rice"
    chef: "Cast iron sear or oven roast, finish and plate"

technique_vocabulary:
  sous_vide:
    - "Drop vacuum-sealed [item] into sous vide bath"
    - "Chef will set temperature remotely from the app"
    - "Remove from bag, reserve juices"
    - "Pat completely dry before searing"
  
  finishing:
    - "Using a kitchen torch, sear until crust forms"
    - "Char on both sides until deeply golden"
    - "Reduce over medium-high heat until thickened into a glaze"
    - "Scraping up browned bits"
  
  plating:
    - "Arrange as a bed/base"
    - "Nestle [item] alongside/on top"
    - "Fan sliced [protein]"
    - "Drizzle [sauce] over"
    - "Scatter [garnish] on top"

linking_external_recipes:
  when: "For complex sub-recipes (bread, specialty techniques)"
  format: "[Recipe Name](URL)"
  example: "[King Arthur No-Knead Rustic Whole Wheat Bread Instructions](https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/)"
  placement: "Within Sous Chef section where timing is relevant"

special_notes:
  cutting_instructions:
    importance: "Be specific about technique when structure matters"
    examples:
      - "Cut through the core/root end so each wedge holds together"
      - "Slice against the grain"
      - "½-inch thick rings"
  
  remote_control:
    sous_vide_apps: "Note when Chef sets temperature remotely"
    timing: "Allows sous chef to focus on prep without worrying about settings"
  markdown_purity:
    - "Let Markdown formatting (bold, italic, strikethrough, blockquotes) render naturally; do not repurpose them as parsing landmarks."
  
  markdown_emphasis_conventions:
    bold: "**text** -- All ingredient names throughout Description and instructions"
    italic: "*text* -- Sensory cues, technique emphasis, timing qualifiers (e.g., *ripping hot*, *low*, *charred and golden*)"
    bold_italic: "***text*** -- Critical action moments only: ***Taste***, ***probe***. Used sparingly."

actions:
  - type: enforce
    when: "Writing or editing meal instructions"
    do:
      - "Use the three base phases for every recipe; additional H3 sections (e.g., ### Leftovers) may follow"
      - "Use H3 headings for each phase (no colons)"
      - "Format Already Prepped as bulleted list"
      - "Format Sous Chef and Chef sections as paragraphs"
      - "Be specific about delegation boundaries"
      - "Include sensory and visual cues"
  
  - type: guide
    when: "Brainstorming new recipes"
    do:
      - "Think through the workflow first"
      - "Identify what can be prepped ahead"
      - "Consider what family members can handle"
      - "Reserve final techniques for primary cook"
      - "Plan for minimal equipment/dish usage"
  
  - type: suggest
    when: "User describes a recipe conversationally"
    do:
      - "Parse the workflow into three phases"
      - "Clarify delegation points"
      - "Add specific timing and temperatures"
      - "Format according to standards"

examples:
  minimal_delegation:
    name: "One Pot Pasta"
    already_prepped: "Just thawed protein"
    sous_chef: "Complete cooking"
    chef: "Serve and plate"
  
  moderate_delegation:
    name: "Stir Fry"
    already_prepped: "Thawed protein"
    sous_chef: "Start rice, prep all ingredients (slice, chop)"
    chef: "High-heat cooking, saucing, plating"
  
  advanced_delegation:
    name: "Sous Vide Steak Dinner"
    already_prepped: "Steaks and vegetables vacuum sealed and pre-cooked"
    sous_chef: "Start sous vide baths, roast vegetables, prep garnishes"
    chef: "Torch-sear protein, char vegetables, make sauce, composed plating"
  
  complex_multitasking:
    name: "Chicken Fricassée"
    already_prepped: "Spatchcocked chicken, cooked beets, bread dough"
    sous_chef: "Sous vide proteins, bake bread, chop greens, prep garnish"
    chef: "Roast chicken to crisp skin, make sauce, shred meat, composed plating"

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
  scope: All recipe instructions in FOOD-OF-THE-WEEK.md and brainstorming files

</rule>
